## Critical Rules ⚠️

### 1. Freezed 3.x - ABSTRACT KEYWORD REQUIRED

**⚠️ CRITICAL**: Always add `abstract` keyword before class definition in Freezed 3.x

```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Missing 'abstract' keyword
@freezed
class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState with _${{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState {
  const factory {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState.initial() = {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormInitial;
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Includes 'abstract' keyword
@freezed
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState with _${{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState {
  const factory {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState.initial() = {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormInitial;
  const factory {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState.loading() = {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormLoading;
  const factory {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState.data({{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Entity {{PRIMARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}) = {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormData;
  const factory {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormState.error(String message) = {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}FormError;
}
```

**Why**: Freezed 3.x requires the `abstract` keyword to properly generate immutable union types.

**Dependencies**:
```yaml
dependencies:
  freezed_annotation: ^{{FREEZED_ANNOTATION_VERSION}}

dev_dependencies:
  freezed: ^{{FREEZED_VERSION}}
  build_runner: ^{{BUILD_RUNNER_VERSION}}
```

