### 3. Repository Segregation Pattern

**⚠️ CRITICAL**: Repositories are segregated by operation type, NOT by entity

Each entity type has multiple repository interfaces, each with a single responsibility:

#### {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}} Repositories (4 interfaces)
```dart
// lib/domain/repositories/{{SECONDARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}/

// Read operations only
abstract class {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ReadRepository {
  Future<List<{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Entity>> getActive{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Plural({{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Type type);
}

// Write operations only
abstract class {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}WriteRepository {
  Future<{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Entity> add{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}({{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Entity {{SECONDARY_ENTITY_LOWER}});
}

// Management operations only (deactivate, reorder)
abstract class {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ManagementRepository {
  Future<void> deactivate{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}(int id);
}

// Seeding operations only
abstract class {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}SeedingRepository {
  Future<void> seedDefault{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Plural();
}
```

#### {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}} Repositories (6+ interfaces)
```dart
// lib/domain/repositories/{{PRIMARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}/

// Basic CRUD
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ReadRepository { }
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}WriteRepository { }

// Query operations
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}QueryRepository { }

// Search operations
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}SearchRepository { }

// Analytics operations
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}AnalyticsRepository { }

// Export operations
abstract class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ExportRepository { }
```

**Why**: This follows the **Interface Segregation Principle (ISP)** - clients only depend on methods they actually use.

**Usage Example**:
```dart
// In a provider that only needs to read {{SECONDARY_ENTITY_PLURAL}}
@riverpod
class {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier extends _${{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier {
  @override
  Future<List<{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Entity>> build() async {
    // Only depends on read repository
    final readRepo = ref.read({{SECONDARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}ReadRepositoryProvider);
    return await readRepo.getActive{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}Plural({{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Type.{{SECONDARY_ENTITY}});
  }
}
```

